######################################################################
# UNIGNORE EMBEDDED COMPOSER FILES
#
# Only where composer had installed vendor/**/vendor WITH composer.lock files,
# to ensure git tracking of those files, and not ignore them by the general /vendor/* rule.
# Will require "git add -f" as well.
#
# Useful commands:
# > find vendor -name composer.lock
# > find vendor -name vendor
######################################################################

!/vendor/paynl/magento-plugin/app/code/community/Pay/Payment/composer.lock
!/vendor/paynl/magento-plugin/app/code/community/Pay/Payment/composer.json


######################################################################
# UNIGNORE ALL CORE HACKED FILES TO ENSURE GIT TRACKING
#
# - CORE HACKS AGAINST COMPOSER-MANAGED PACKAGES are tracked by git
#   through composer patch files OR by adding the hacked files to git and
#   documenting them in COREHACKS.md.
#
# - HACKS TO 3RD PARTY PACKAGES THAT ARE NOT MANAGED BY COMPOSER do
#   NOT need patches. For those, either use a forked VCS repo or, if
#   no more updates are expected from any 3rd party, just add them
#   directly to the codebase and track them with git, and document
#   them in COREHACKS.md.
#
# Useful commands:
#
# 1. Find symlinks in places where OpenMage installs its extensions:
#    > find app/code/ lib/ -type l | sort -f
#    Core hacks in symlinked files MUST BE implemented through the patch system
#    described in AGENTS.md (cweagans/composer-patches). Un-ignoring a single file
#    does nothing if the file's parent is a symlink to a file in vendor/ that is not tracked by git.
#
# 2. Find all files with DHH or CORE HACK in them:
#    > grep -rilI -e DHH -e "CORE HACK" . | sort -f
#
# ..which must be the same list as:
#
# 3. Find all differences with the original Magento LTS codebase:
#    > diff -qr . vendor/openmage/magento-lts | sort -f
#    > diff -qr vendor/openmage/magento-lts . | sort -f
######################################################################

# grep -rilI -e DHH -e "CORE HACK" app/*.* | sort -f
# diff -qr app/*.* vendor/openmage/magento-lts/app/*.* | sort -f
